SUMMARY:An Acoustic Celebration of the Grateful Dead and Bob Weir
DESCRIPTION:On January 10\, 2026\, after approximately 4\,500 live performances spanning 7 decades\, Grateful Dead guitarist Bob Weir passed away. The Cloverdale Arts Alliance and Americana Night are honoring his legacy with this Acoustic Celebration of the Grateful Dead and Bob Weir. \nOur all-star lineup for the evening features Jay Wilcox\, Zach Jones and Jeff Quigley of the Lovin’ Dead\, Matt Petruska of Flowstone\, and Rhyne Erde of Electric Tumbleweed. As Bob once famously told David Letterman\, this will be “more fun than a frog in a glass of milk.” \nWe will be eliminating some of our usual seats in the back to make room for dancing. Nothing left to do but smile\, smile\, smile.
URL:https://golocal.coop/event/an-acoustic-celebration-of-the-grateful-dead-and-bob-weir/
LOCATION:Cloverdale Arts Alliance\, 204 N. Cloverdale Blvd.\, Cloverdale\, CA
CATEGORIES:Music
GEO:38.8071;-123.018
X-APPLE-STRUCTURED-LOCATION;VALUE=URI;X-ADDRESS=Cloverdale Arts Alliance 204 N. Cloverdale Blvd. Cloverdale CA;X-APPLE-RADIUS=500;X-TITLE=204 N. Cloverdale Blvd.:geo:-123.018,38.8071
END:VEVENT
